1. Terminology:
- 
- Node: A node is an instance of the Docker engine participating in the swarm.
  - Manager node:
    - dispatches units of work called tasks to worker nodes.
    - perform the orchestration and cluster management functions required to
      maintain the desired state of the swarm.
    - only an single elected leader to conduct orchestration tasks.
  - Worker node:
    - receive and execute tasks dispatched from manager nodes.
    - by default, manager node also runs service of worker node.
- Service: is the definition of the tasks to execute on the manager or worker
  nodes.
  - Replicated service: distribute a specific number of replica tasks among the
    nodes.
  - Global service: run on all available nodes.
- Task: carries a Docker container and the commands to run inside the container.
- Load balancing:
  - Ingress load balancing
